    <h2>Oboe D'amore</h2>
    <div class="row content" id="b-damore-contents">
      <div class="col-md-6">
           <p> The oboe d'amore is a transposing instrument in A, which
             appears mostly in the music of J.S Bach. Telemann also wrote
             many solos for this instrument. After the death of Bach in 1650
              it seemed to have been forgotten, as there is no evidence that
              it was composed for or played. The instrument has a beautiful
              rounded, mellow sound. The sound was developed, by creating a
              wider bore and spreading the tone holes further apart. It is
              distinguished by its resonant rounded bell. Her instrument 'Woody'
               is a copy of an Eichantopf, made by Sand Dalton. You can see where
                he gets his name from, if you look at the beautiful patterns in
                 the wood.
           </p>
